HEADWORD: Thinly
<hw>Thin"ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>In a thin manner; in a
loose, scattered manner; scantily; not thickly; <as>as, ground
<ex>thinly</ex> planted with trees; a country <ex>thinly</ex>
inhabited.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

